OL,6,FMartin Strutton, Shelterbox response
OL,7,Fteam lead said: "Where the flood water
OL,8,Fis starting to recede, it's revealing
OL,9,Fthe true scale of damage to homes and
OL,10,Fbelongings that many people don't have
OL,11,Fthe resources to repair or replace."
OL,13,FHe added that the team have been able
OL,14,Fto respond "relatively quickly," as
OL,15,Faid was stored in a warehouse
OL,16,Ffollowing Cyclone Freddy in 2023,
OL,17,Fwhich killed more than 400 people.
